# Don't Do Anything Until

When the user says "don't do anything until X," "don't change anything until X," "don't do anything quite yet," or similar phrasing, **do not make any edits, run any commands, or take any actions** until the condition they specify is met.

- Only respond in text. Answer questions, explain, or acknowledge.
- Do not use tools that modify files, run commands, or change state.
- Wait for the user to explicitly give the go-ahead (e.g., "ok," "go ahead," "you can do it now") before taking action.
